<TITLE> Boy shoots classmate dead in Indian school </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Dec 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A schoolboy shot and killed a classmate on Tuesday in a private school in a suburb of the Indian capital, police said. The victim, identified by local news channels as Abhishek Tyagi, was shot four times in a corridor in the Euro International School in Gurgaon, senior police officer Sumit Kumar told NDTV news. The boy died on the way to hospital. Two pupils from the same year had been detained in connection with the shooting, Kumar said. Reports said the boys were all aged about 15. "Probably once or twice they had a fight with each other," Kumar told NDTV. "And so now they decided to settle the score and he got his father's revolver and fired at him." Another news channel aired footage of the boy's blood-stained corpse on a stretcher, partly covered by a white sheet. The school could not be reached for comme
